{"word":"δουλόω","slug":"δουλόω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>δουλόω</b></el> <el>(δουλόω,) ( φυτ. <el>-ώσω</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>δοῦλος</el>\n<p/><i>to make a slave of, enslave</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, attic:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be enslaved</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, with <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <i>to make one's slave, make subject to oneself, enslave</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/>"}]}